{
  "id": "019d32c8-c07e-7cc1-9e70-7fd3377d6369",
  "content": "# BM25 Tantivy Integration (Phase 2a) -- Design Decisions\n\n## What: Add full-text BM25 search to LiteStore via embedded tantivy with code-aware tokenization.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. **FullTextSearchable trait in traits.rs** -- algorithm-agnostic naming (search_text not search_bm25). Async trait with flush() default no-op. Returns lightweight TextSearchResult(entry_id, score) to keep FTS decoupled from full entry storage.\n2. **TantivyIndex as cache, not truth** -- stored in .corvia/cache/tantivy/, fully rebuildable from knowledge JSON files. Schema: content (TEXT), entry_id (STRING), scope_id (STRING), content_role (STRING), source_origin (STRING).\n3. **Code-aware custom tokenizer (\"corvia_code\")** -- splits snake_case, CamelCase, file paths, UUIDs, version strings while preserving originals. All tokens lowercased.\n4. **Batched commit strategy** -- buffer via add_document(), auto-flush every 100 entries or 500ms (tokio timer). Single commit on rebuild. IndexReader::reload() after each flush.\n5. **Write-generation staleness** -- monotonic fts_write_generation in Redb META table, last_synced_generation in JSON alongside tantivy index. Startup comparison triggers rebuild on mismatch.\n6. **LiteStore holds Option<TantivyIndex>** -- None when BM25 not configured (zero cost). insert() and delete_scope() mirror to tantivy when present.\n7. **Bm25Searcher implements Searcher trait** -- needs_embedding()=false, uses SearchContext.query for text search. Registered as \"bm25\" in PipelineRegistry.\n\n## Alternatives rejected:\n- External BM25 process via JSONL IPC -- too much overhead for embedded use case\n- Feature-gated tantivy -- start without feature flag, add only if compile time > 45s\n- Synchronous commit per write -- too slow for bulk ingest, batched approach is standard tantivy pattern",
  "source_version": "mcp",
